- cs.GT (Game Theory) is likely because the paper discusses the auction model used in real-time bidding and the competition among media buyers, which are typical topics in game theory.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is likely because the paper proposes a model that involves inventory control theory and dynamic reserve prices, which are related to data structures and algorithms for efficient resource allocation.
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is likely because the paper deals with the interaction and negotiation between media sellers and buyers, which can be modeled as a multi-agent system.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible because the paper may involve some machine learning techniques for predicting future supply and demand of ad views.
